Permission is granted to students, educators, and academic researchers globally (except those users in the Philippines and those considered Philippine-based users, as described in section II) to use Covary-encoder for non-profit and non-commercial academic or research purposes only.  

The following are strictly prohibited without prior written permission or license from the copyright holder:
  • Commercial use of any kind  
  • Modification or creation of derivative works  
  • Redistribution or sublicensing of the code  
  • Incorporation into other software or services  

II. Philippine-based Users
A Philippine-based user is any user whose interests, affiliations, residency, or activities are connected to the Philippines materially, philosophically, or otherwise. All users considered Philippine-based users must obtain a valid license from the copyright holder prior to any use of Covary-encoder, in any form such as research, education, commercial, testing, or otherwise. Philippine-based users inlcude, but are not limited to the following:
1. Users physically located in the Philippines: Any user who is physically present in the Philippines while accessing or using Covary-encoder, regardless of IP geolocation.
2. Users with Philippine-based affiliations or place of work: Users employed, enrolled, or officially affiliated with a Philippine institution, organization, or company, regardless of their current location.
3. Users whose organization is global but whose work location or designation is in the Philippines: Users working for international organizations but performing duties from a Philippine location or designated as Philippine-based.
4. International collaborations involving Philippine users: Any joint project, research, or sharing of Covary-encoder that involves users, institutions, or facilities in the Philippines. All Philippine participants must hold a valid license, even if collaborators are outside the Philippines.
5. Philippine residents traveling abroad temporarily (without affiliations outside the Philippines): Residents of the Philippines using Covary-encoder while temporarily outside the Philippines are still considered Philippine-based users and must hold a valid license to use Covary-encoder.
6. Users within organizations owned by Philippine-based entities: Any user who is a member, employee, affiliate, or contractor of an organization (whether local or international) that is wholly or partially owned, managed, or controlled by a Philippine-based user.

Any user meeting the Philippine-based definition, requires a valid license, regardless of the user’s current location, organization, or circumstances.

III. Unauthorized use and automatic license conversion
Any use of Covary-encoder outside the permissions, limitations, or scope expressly granted under this license shall constitute unauthorized use. By engaging in unauthorized use, the user agrees and acknowledges that:
1. Such use shall be deemed an election to operate under a premium commercial license, effective from the date of first unauthorized use;
2. The user shall be obligated to pay all applicable fees associated with such premium license, including retroactive fees covering the period of unauthorized use;
3. Applicable fees shall be determined according to:
  - the then-current published pricing of the copyright holder, or
  - a separately issued invoice or licensing agreement provided by the copyright holder.

Failure to remit payment upon notice constitutes a material breach of this license and may result in termination of rights, revocation of access, and pursuit of legal remedies.

